<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> (Wells 1999)</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> (Bryant 2000)</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/15/science/15writing.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/15/science/15writing.html" rel="nofollow">"Writing May Be Oldest in Western Hemisphere."</a>. <a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/15/science/15writing.html" class="external free" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/15/science/15writing.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/15/science/15writing.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-30</span>.  "A stone slab bearing 3,000-year-old writing previously unknown to scholars has been found in the Mexican state of Veracruz, and archaeologists say it is an example of the oldest script ever discovered in the Western Hemisphere."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Writing+May+Be+Oldest+in+Western+Hemisphere.&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNew+York+Times%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2006%2F09%2F15%2Fscience%2F15writing.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Writing"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5347080.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5347080.stm" rel="nofollow">"'Oldest' New World writing found"</a>. <a href="/wiki/BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5347080.stm" class="external free" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5347080.stm" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5347080.stm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-30</span>.  "Ancient civilisations in Mexico developed a writing system as early as 900 BC, new evidence suggests."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%27Oldest%27+New+World+writing+found&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BBBC%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F2%2Fhi%2Fscience%2Fnature%2F5347080.stm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Writing"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/313/5793/1610" class="external text" title="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/313/5793/1610" rel="nofollow">"Oldest Writing in the New World"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Science" title="Science">Science</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/313/5793/1610" class="external free" title="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/313/5793/1610" rel="nofollow">http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/313/5793/1610</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-30</span>.  "A block with a hitherto unknown system of writing has been found in the Olmec heartland of Veracruz, Mexico. Stylistic and other dating of the block places it in the early first millennium before the common era, the oldest writing in the New World, with features that firmly assign this pivotal development to the Olmec civilization of Mesoamerica."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Oldest+Writing+in+the+New+World&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BScience%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencemag.org%2Fcgi%2Fcontent%2Fabstract%2F313%2F5793%2F1610&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Writing"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
